SEARCH
Package model

Class Project

java.lang.Object
model.Project
public class Project extends Object
The "Project" class represents a research project with various attributes such as researcher name, project type, status, name, identifier, description, initial date, and end date.

    • addEvidence

      public void addEvidence(String evidenceName, String evidenceDescription, String evidenceType, String evidenceLocation, String evidenceDate, String evidenceTime, String evidenceResearcherName, String evidencePilarType, String evidenceProyectName, String evidenceProyectIdentifier, String evidenceProyectDescription, String evidenceProyectInitialDate, String evidenceProyectEndDate)
      The function "addEvidence" is used to add evidence to a system, taking in various parameters such as evidence name, description, type, location, date, time, researcher name, and project details.
      Parameters:
      evidenceName - The name of the evidence being added.
      evidenceDescription - The description of the evidence.
      evidenceType - The type of evidence, such as document, photo, video, etc.
      evidenceLocation - The location where the evidence was found or collected.
      evidenceDate - The evidenceDate parameter is a string that represents the date when the evidence was collected or recorded.
      evidenceTime - The evidenceTime parameter is used to specify the time at which the evidence was collected or recorded. It can be in any format that represents time, such as "HH:mm" or "hh:mm a".
      evidenceResearcherName - The name of the researcher who collected the evidence.
      evidencePilarType - The evidencePilarType parameter represents the type or category of the evidence within a specific framework or system. It could be used to classify the evidence based on different criteria or aspects.
      evidenceProyectName - The name of the project that the evidence is related to.
      evidenceProyectIdentifier - The evidenceProyectIdentifier parameter is used to identify the project associated with the evidence. It could be a unique identifier or a reference to the project in a database.
      evidenceProyectDescription - The evidenceProyectDescription parameter is a string that represents the description of the project associated with the evidence.
      evidenceProyectInitialDate - The evidenceProyectInitialDate parameter represents the initial date of the project related to the evidence.
      evidenceProyectEndDate - The parameter "evidenceProyectEndDate" represents the end date of the project associated with the evidence.

    • registerProyect

      public void registerProyect(String researchername, String pilarType, String proyectStatus, String proyectName, String proyectIdentifier, String proyectDescription, String initialDate, String endDate)
      The function "registerProyect" is used to register a new project with various details such as researcher name, project type, status, name, identifier, description, initial date, and end date.
      Parameters:
      researchername - The name of the researcher who is registering the project.
      pilarType - The type of pillar the project belongs to. Examples could be "Education", "Healthcare", "Environment", etc.
      proyectStatus - The proyectStatus parameter represents the current status of the project. It could be "ongoing", "completed", "cancelled", or any other relevant status.
      proyectName - The name of the project.
      proyectIdentifier - The proyectIdentifier parameter is used to uniquely identify a project. It could be a unique identifier such as a project ID or a combination of letters and numbers that is unique to each project.
      proyectDescription - The proyectDescription parameter is a String that represents the description of the project. It provides information about the purpose, goals, and scope of the project.
      initialDate - The initial date of the project.
      endDate - The endDate parameter represents the date when the project is expected to be completed or finished.

    • modifyProyect

      public void modifyProyect(String researchername, String pilarType, String proyectStatus, String proyectName, String proyectIdentifier, String proyectDescription, String initialDate, String endDate)
      The function "modifyProyect" takes in various parameters to modify a project's details.
      Parameters:
      researchername - The name of the researcher working on the project.
      pilarType - The type of pillar the project belongs to (e.g. social, economic, environmental).
      proyectStatus - The status of the project (e.g. ongoing, completed, cancelled)
      proyectName - The name of the project that you want to modify.
      proyectIdentifier - The proyectIdentifier parameter is a unique identifier for the project. It could be a string or an integer value that distinguishes the project from others.
      proyectDescription - The proyectDescription parameter is a String that represents the description of the project. It provides information about the purpose, goals, and scope of the project.
      initialDate - The initial date of the project.
      endDate - The endDate parameter represents the date when the project is expected to be completed or finished.

    • addEvidence

      public void addEvidence(String evidenceName, String evidenceDescription, String fileURL, String relatedProject, String associatedPointInterest, Calendar registrationDate)
      The function adds evidence with the given details to a system.
      Parameters:
      evidenceName - The name of the evidence being added. This could be a title or a brief description of the evidence.
      evidenceDescription - The evidence description is a string that provides additional details or information about the evidence being added.
      fileURL - The fileURL parameter is a string that represents the URL or file path of the evidence file.
      relatedProject - The relatedProject parameter is used to specify the project or task that the evidence is associated with.
      associatedPointInterest - The associatedPointInterest parameter refers to the specific point of interest or topic that the evidence is related to. It could be a specific feature, requirement, or aspect of the project that the evidence supports or provides information about.
      registrationDate - The registrationDate parameter is of type Calendar and represents the date when the evidence is registered.
